question:
As <b>useState</b> is not a synchronous operation, instead of just relying on using some state property like <code>state.counter</code>, it is better to use the <b>prev state</b> pattern, that will always provide the latest state values. Refactor the below set state method so it uses <b>prev state</b> for updating the counter to be equals <code>+1</code>. (Remeber that it needs also its props as an argument).
<pre>this.setState({
	counter: this.state.counter + 1
});</pre>
